  "texts": [
    "In the original paper by Mata and Ringach 45 on-and off-subunits also contained regions suppressed by bright and dark stimuli respectively.",
    "We assumed that the phosphenes elicited by electrical stimulation reflected only the excitatory components of the receptive fields.",
    "Separations (δ on/off, normalized by receptive field area) between the on and off subunits of each receptive field were drawn from an exponential distribution, such that small separations were common and large separations were rare, with the rate of fall-off designed to match neurophysiological data 45.",
    "The same 2-D complex-valued white noise image as were used to generate ocular dominance and orientation columns 46 was bandpass filtered with a radial Gabor of frequency 2 ω F = 1.726.",
    "The angle, u, of the resulting complex-valued image (which had a flat distribution) was converted to distance between the on and off subunits:"
  ],
